nfrared]] [[radiation]] from [[ozone]], [[water vapor]], [[Haloalkane|CFC]]s, [[methane]] and [[nitrogen]] compounds. Developed jointly with the [[United Kingdom]] [[Natural Environment Research Council]]. The HIRDLS chopper shutdown on March 17, 2008, and has not produced science since.\n*'''MLS \u2014 [[Microwave Limb Sounder]]''' \u2014 measures emissions from ozone, [[chlorine]] and other [[trace gases]], and clarifies the role of water vapor in [[global warming]].\n*'''OMI \u2014 [[Ozone Monitoring Instrument]]''' \u2014 uses [[ultraviolet]] and [[light|visible radiation]] to produce daily high-resolution [[map]]s. Developed by the [[Finnish Meteorological Institute]]  and the [[Netherlands Agency for Aerospace Programmes]].\n*'''TES \u2014 [[Tropospheric Emission Spectrometer]]''' \u2014 measures [[tropospheric]] ozone in infrared [[wavelength]]s, also [[carbon monoxide]], methane and [[NOx|nitrogen oxides]].\n\n==See also==\n*[[Terra (satellite)|Terra]]\n*[[Aqua (satellite)|Aqua]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://aura.gsfc.nasa.gov/index.html NASA site]\n*[http://avdc.gsfc.nasa.gov/Overview/news.html Aura validation data centre]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20070802045158/http://solarsystem.nasa.gov/missions/profile.cfm?MCode=AURA Aura Mission Profile] by [http://solarsystem.nasa.gov NASA's Solar System Exploration]\n\n{{Space-based meteorological observation}}\n{{Orbital launches in 2004}}\n\n[[Category:Earth observation satellites]]\n[[Category:Spacecraft launched in 2004]]\n[[Category:Spacecraft launched by Delta II rockets]]"}]}}}}